                    .col-md-6
                        h3 What is RF?
                        p Specialized RF generators can produce electircal impulses that alternate direction at more than 500 Mhz. Using expertly placed probes, these  pulses can be directed at problematic nerves with clinical accuracy. The current runs right through the body, and returns via a dispersive plate placed on the back of the patients leg.
                    .col-md-6.text-center
                        img(src="img/Rf.png")
                h3.pt-3 How does it manage pain?
                p At extremely high frequencies, ions oscilating in the body cause friction at an atomic level. This friction generates heat which leads to micriscopic lesions in the targeted nerve. These lesions then trigger the restorative processes which address pain right at the source.
                .container.text-center.pt-5
                    img.w-100(src="img/RFtreatment.png")
                    p RF treatment being performed at The Helderberg Pain Clinic
